I am clumsy and I spill stuff but It looks same as the day I bought it. I've probably jinxed it now. Would definitely get another if I lost it. Haven't used Windows for about 14 years so no idea how it compares to mac. I want to turn the laptop on and it be ready to use straight away, I want no involvement in the computer's operation, I don't want to be bothered with updates, patches etc. If that is still a thing with windows I am not interested. I put that stuff behind me in 2007.

snippet.textDisplay:
It looks (on the outside) just like a slightly refined version of the 2015 Macbook air... I have been using my girlfriend's 2015 Macbook air for the last 2 years. I wanted to upgrade but decided to wait until Quad core CPU's entered the Macbook Air lineup. I'm glad I waited so long because, as a daily driver NOTHING comes close to my (albeit old) Macbook air. The typing experience is second to none. The trackpad is second to none. The battery life is amazing. Build quality is superb.
This is the upgrade most people were waiting for.
MKBHD - just do it, make the Macbook Air your daily driver, do it for the keyboard man! >_<
